<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=4934&amp;p=21964#p21964"><![CDATA[
Version 4.2.4 does not support making the Metro skin in Windows 7 style transparent. A future version might support this. In &quot;Classic with two columns&quot; style, you can make it transparent. Go to the Skin tab and uncheck &quot;Disable glass transparency&quot;. If on Windows 10, you don't want glass but just transparency, go to the Menu Look tab and uncheck &quot;Enable menu glass&quot;.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Tue Sep 08, 2015 9:11 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
